str2: And not, not even, neither?nor. From me and de; but not, not even; in a continued negation, nor.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To exercise authority over, overpower, master. From kata and kurieuo; to lord against, i.e. Control, subjugate.
(a) a lot, (b) a portion assigned; hence: a portion of the people of God assigned to one's care, a congregation.
But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
From tupto; a die, i.e. a stamp or scar; by analogy, a shape, i.e. A statue, style or resemblance; specially, a sampler, i.e. A model or instance.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A little flock. Neuter of a presumed derivative of poimne; a flock, i.e. group.
